shorthands
    - for <div class="main-content"> you can type div.main-content

body
    - 'color' on body sets the color of all the elements on the webpage
        - all the text on the page unless already specified
        - elements like anchor tags which have their own prespecified css remain 
        unaffected
        - can be text or a # number
    - font-family
        - font such as arial
    - max-width
    - 2 ways to space things
        - margin 
            - 0 auto;
                - no margin on top or bottom
                - auto adjust for left and right
            - everything OUTSIDE highlighted area
        - padding
            - 0 16px;
                - no padding above or below
                - 16px between body content and side of browser window
            - everything inside highlighted area

setting a sticky footer - flexbox
    - wrap all contents except footer in div element
    - then, use flexbox to let this div take up all the available space
    - css   
        - display: flex;
        - flex-direction: column;
        - min-height = 100vh; (100% of the viewport height)
        - then on the directed class, use flex-grow: 1;
        